EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value is how many years your practice hour requirement is based on (eg: if you require 1000 hours every 5 years, you would put 5 as this value). This assumes your practice hour requirement is rolling, if the practice hour requirement is tied to the active CCP cycle then set this value to -1.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'PracticeHourInterval'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value is how many practice hours your practice hour requirement is based on (eg: if you require 1000 hours every 5 years, you would put 1000 as this value).', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'PracticeHourRequirement'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value is appended onto messages where an unexpected error has occurred in the program but the application is able to recover and keep running. The text should advise the user what to do in this scenario. Normally this will include retrying the process and contacting the help desk if the error persists. While product help desk support is generally provided to licensed administrators only, program errors can be reported by any user.  The option to report the problem with the local administrator may also be helpful. Note that a separate suffix is available for "configuration" errors.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'ProgramErrorSuffix'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value controls whether or not search by registrant no is allowed on the public directory.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'PUB_DIR_RegNoEnabled'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value is used to configure which filters are available on the public directory. The filter types must be separated by a comma and is limited to only the filters configured in the product (eg: "PRACTICEREGISTER,EFFECTIVETIME"). Contact Softworks support for assistance when modifying this value.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'PublicDirectoryFilters'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value controls the maximum number of records the application will return when a search is executed on the Public Directory.  The limit is applied on Employer and Member directory features if configured.  Limiting search results is good practice to discourage inappropriate use of your data by individuals who might seek to download large lists of member information to use for direct marketing or even to apply in identity theft schemes.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'PublicDirectoryRowLimit'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This controls whether or not the public registry is available in the client portal.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'PublicRegistryConfigured'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value established the threshold the application uses for "Recently Accessed" searches.  Many screens in the application provide a quick search where the application returns a list of records that have been recently accessed by the user.  The definition of "recent" is defined using this parameter in units of hours.  The default value is 24 hours; meaning that any record where details have been retrieved by that user within the last 24 hours will be included in "recently accessed" search results. Note that, by default, weekends are not included in the 24 period but this can be controlled using the "Exclude Weekends for Recent Access" configuration option.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'RecentAccessHours'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'The lowest number that should be generated for new registrants. This values sets the starting point for new registration numbers to assign.  The value is NOT updated once registration numbers start being assigned. The number range must be distinct from converted registration numbers and new Application numbers if using both Application and Registration number sequences. Contact the Help Desk for assistance with setting this value.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'RegistrantNoMinimum'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'A template controlling the format of the registrant number. Example: "R####" results in R1001, R1002, etc. Any letter prefix or suffix may be used with “#” indicating number of digits. The minimum number of digits is 4. To avoid assigning this number until applicants have achieved their first Active-Practice registration, you must also define an Applicant# Template. Contact the Help Desk for assistance with setting this value.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'RegistrantNoTemplate'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This is the email address used by the system to send email to users and administrators. The email address must bevalid and verified to use the distribution method is configured in email setup:  Amazon SES or SMTP. The accountneed not accept replies.  End users see this address when reading mail messages sent by the application.  If adifferent reply-to address is not specified in email setup, this will be the reply address by default.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'SenderEmail'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This configuration option shows or hides the logged in registrant''s current registration from the client portal.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'ShowLicensesToRegistrant'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This controls whether or not the advanced linking features for notes is available in the user interface.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'ShowNoteLinkOptions'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This text is displayed to the applicant during sign up, this is informative text letting the applicant know what they are signing up for.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'SignupMessage'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This controls whether the Specializations assigned to members require that a granting organization be specified. Otherwise a granting organization is optional.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'SpecializationsReqOrgs'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value is applied to standard auditing columns ("created by", "updated by") when changes are made to the database by automated batch processes such as importing data from external sources. The value is not a licensed user account and cannot be used to login.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'SystemUser'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'The technical help desk number is displayed in the application to give users a number to call when they have technical issues.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'TechnicalHelpDeskNumber'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value controls how long (in hours) a pending trial request will wait for confirmation by the user.  During this period no other potential tenants can attempt to reserve the same sub-domain, tenant name etc. so that duplication is avoided.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'TenantReservationHours'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'The maximum number of minutes the application should be allowed to remain idle for external users before requiring another login.This is a security parameter that requires that the user to login again after the set period of inactivity. This prevents users from leaving logged workstations accessible for long periods of time to passers-by. Note that inactive time is measured as the gap between database accesses. Simple mouse movement is not sufficient to restart the idle-time clock.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'TimeOut'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This text is displayed to the registrant during sign up. The registrant must agree to these terms before they are able to use Alinity™.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'TOSRegistrant'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'When set to on this will cause e-mail sent from the system to include a beacon image that will allow, in most cases, the ability to record when a particular e-mail was opened. Do note that many e-mail clients may refuse to open images or will strip off any tracking information before opening the image and therefore the system will be unable to determine if e-mails to those clients have been opened.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'TrackEmailOpens'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'The maximum number of days a user account can go without logging in, before it is identified for follow-up as a possible unused account.  A built-in task trigger (enabled by default) creates follow-up tasks for accounts that have been unused for this number of days.  Removing unused accounts from the system is a security best-practice.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'UnusedAccountWarningDays'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value is used to identify User Accounts that require review.  User Accounts should be reviewed periodically to ensure they are still required and that access provided to the user remains appropriate.  The target interval between reviews is specified in months .  When an account has not been reviewed within the period defined, an icon appears to mark the record overdue and these accounts can also be accessed through a built-in query.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'UserProfileReviewMonths'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value defines the list of email domains that will be considered valid by the application. This is a comma delimited list: e.g. ".com, .ca, .edu" (no quotes).  If a domain is entered on an email address that is not in the list, and that business rule is enabled, then an error is raised and the email address cannot be saved. The purpose of this value is to improve accuracy and reliability of email addresses managed in the application. To allow email addresses from any domain, either turn the business rule off in the configuration or set this value to "*" (no quotes).', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'ValidEmailDomains'
GO
EXEC sp_addextendedproperty N'MS_Description', N'This value controls the number of years a member on an Inactive Register (inactive status) will appear on the Public Directory. The limit is applied on Employer and Member directory features if configured. To include inactive members on the Directories forever, enter 99.', 'SCHEMA', N'dbo', 'VIEW', N'vConfigParam#Active', 'COLUMN', N'YearsInactiveLimit'
GO
